latestIgtvVideos.title: Waacking- First attempt
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Waacking is a form of club dance created in the LGBT clubs of Los Angeles during the 1970s disco era. The style is typically done to 70s disco music and is mainly distinguishable by its rotational arm movements, posing and emphasis on expressiveness. .
Song- Troyboi 
Camera work- @bgirl_shawtypink ❤️
Waacking basics taught by @riddhiupadhyay21 .

latestPosts.caption:
Express Yourself Ft. @thefitgayunicorn 

Sam smith has been one of the most remarkable artists of our times, for people like me. Their music has helped me embrace this journey of self-acceptance & expression. 

How do you sleep has a different meaning, feeling for me. It makes me realize the need for efforts to embrace myself and offer self-love in this journey of accepting my whole self, so as to simply live, sustain & express. Self expression is such an individualistic yet important way to communicate to the community. Most of us queer folks, find it difficult to find our own style and have to pave our path. Elements like the “blindfold” and use of leather represents our second skin, chains represent the shackles and restrictions placed on us by the society not just as a queer person but also by way of gender roles, what we wear, how we speak, how we move. 

This is to everyone out there to celebrate this journey of revealing & embracing our sexuality much more than ever. Here’s wishing everyone support and space to start celebrating their dreams. Slay the most out of this beautiful journey!
